<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 02 at 9:20AM CDT  by NWS Central Illinois</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Christian, south
central Sangamon, northwestern Shelby and southern Macon Counties
through 945 AM CDT...
At 919 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Stonington, or 8 miles north of Taylorville, moving south at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Taylorville around 925 AM CDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Pana.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
